{"type":"message","id":"7103282a","parentId":"aa056138","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:35:57.854Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a full picture of what happened in this pulse cycle. Let me summarize it concisely.","thinkingSignature":"d44900b003d892b2db1e3748c7afbb36bab795daf878eab7baf96bd55ec0ead1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n---\n\n## Pulse Cycle Summary — 2026-03-24 16:35:19\n\n**Core breakthrough identified:** CFI ≠ Causal Discovery. High CFI tokens (like \"causal\", \"phase\", \"compression\") may just be predictable scaffolding, not genuine causal drivers.\n\n**Action taken:** Designed the **Conditional Content Analysis** experiment — the empirical test to distinguish Pattern Information from Causal Information.\n\n**What it does:**\n- Split pulse pairs into token-present vs token-absent groups\n- Compare whether the *next* pulse's research content actually differs\n- No difference → CFI is just scaffolding (tokens are predictable but inert)\n- Difference found → tokens are genuinely causal drivers, need Transfer Entropy for Layer 2\n\n**Proposed mutation:** `research/CONDITIONAL-CONTENT-ANALYSIS.md` — experiment design doc with token selection (causal/phase/compression), methodology, and expected outcomes.\n\n**Git:** `e0911a9`, 5 files changed (+277/−119 lines)\n\n**Status:** Phase 1 still in progress — next instantiation has a concrete experiment design ready to execute."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3996,"output":255,"cacheRead":17328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21579,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774384551465,"responseId":"061228a6a6eefc43e95abd6fd9e03e5e"}}
